The paper deals with the problem of clustering billions of web pages, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The algorithm proposed in the paper is designed to handle large-scale data and uses efficient algorithms, which suggests it could also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of the clustering using novel evaluations, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
